records.addlTxt: Competency hearing on November 14, 2022 at 09:00 am.

2:30 PM cases 22CF877, 22CF918, 22CM539, 22CM587 called and held via Zoom. Defendant Tamyra J. Nelson not in court.  Attorney Michael J Steuer in court for Tamyra J. Nelson.  Attorney Andrew James Gunderson in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant is in Mendota- parties agree since they are needing more time, they are okay with her not appearing for today. 
Court finds Good Cause to extend time limits for the competency hearing to be completed based on letter from the doctor. 
Parties to schedule a competency hearing after 10/27/22.
Dated 10/07/2022, Letter to Court from Emily Peissig, Psy.D., requesting an extension for evaluation.

2:01 PM Cases called: 22CF877, 22CM539, 22CM587 & 22CF918Defendant Tamyra J. Nelson appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Michael J Steuer in court for Tamyra J. Nelson.  Attorney Andrew James Gunderson in court for State of Wisconsin. This is the date and time set for a competency hearing. 
Based on the report filed by the doctor, Court finds good cause that this matter continues and the defendant is ordered to be transported to an inpatient facility for continuation of the competency examination.
